Docs.summary: Represents a method or method-like symbol (including constructor, destructor, operator, or property/event accessor).
Docs.remarks: This interface is reserved for implementation by its associated APIs. We reserve the right to change it in the future.

If this method is a Lambda method (MethodKind = MethodKind.LambdaMethod) and there is an anonymous delegate associated with it, returns this delegate.
Returns null if the symbol is not a lambda or if it does not have an anonymous delegate associated with it.

public: property Microsoft::CodeAnalysis::ISymbol ^ AssociatedSymbol { Microsoft::CodeAnalysis::ISymbol ^ get(); };

Docs.summary: Returns a symbol (e.g. property, event, etc.) associated with the method.
Docs.remarks: If this method has of or , returns the property that this method is the getter or setter for. If this method has of or , returns the event that this method is the adder or remover for. Note, the set of possible associated symbols might be expanded in the future to reflect changes in the languages.

MemberSignature.Value: Public ReadOnly Property IsVararg As Boolean
public: property bool IsVararg { bool get(); };

Docs.summary:
Returns whether this method is using CLI VARARG calling convention. This is used for C-style variable argument lists. This is used extremely rarely in C# code and is represented using the undocumented "__arglist" keyword.
Note that methods with "params" on the last parameter are indicated with the "IsParams" property on ParameterSymbol, and are not represented with this property.
